Aman Resorts, the chain of  luxury
resorts  owned by Indian property company  DLF Ltd. (DLFU) , may be sold
for more than $400 million, the  Sunday Times  reported, without
saying where it got the information.  DLF is seeking a buyer for Aman, whose guests have
included celebrities such as David and Victoria Beckham, and may
have asked Goldman Sachs Group Inc. and Citigroup Inc. to find a
strategic partner, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
